r%20the%20president's%20actions%20have%20historical%20precedent%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20legal%20basis%20%E2%80%94%20the%20verdict%20was%20murky.%20For%20most%20government%20spending%2C%20Congress%20outlines%20what%20are%20called%20%26quot%3Bappropriations%2C%26quot%3B%20very%20specific%20line%20items%20on%20when%20and%20how%20each%20dollar%20should%20be%20spent.%20Any%20attempt%20to%20change%20those%20appropriations%20typically%20requires%20legislative%20approval%2C%20a%20step%20of%20the%20process%20that%20Trump%20has%20been%20bypassing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20Democrats'%20disgusting%20playbook%3A%20inflict%20maximum%20pain%20on%20Americans%20to%20cling%20to%20power%2C%20the%20administration%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Farticles%2F2025%2F10%2Ftop-democrat-cheers-americans-suffering-as-leverage-in-their-sick-political-game%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober%2022%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20President%20Trump%20takes%20decisive%20action%20to%20ensure%20service%20members%20get%20paid%20and%20critical%20nutrition%20assistance%20programs%20for%20low-income%20women%20and%20children%20remain%20funded%2C%20unhinged%20Democrats%20are%20doing%20anything%20they%20can%20to%20stop%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Trump's%20decision%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-paid-during-the-government-shutdown-ice-border-patrol-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%20the%20military%20and%20select%20law%20enforcement%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20shutdown.%20Without%20a%20vote%20in%20Congress%2C%20the%20White%20House%20sent%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Ff%2F%3Fid%3D00000199-f9bb-d346-aff9-fbbf1a8d0000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober%2017%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20stating%20that%20%26quot%3BIn%20such%20a%20dire%20circumstance%20as%20this%2C%20where%20there%20is%20no%20other%20appropriation%20providing%20for%20payment%20of%20military%20salaries%2C%20and%20where%20failure%20to%20pay%20our%20troops%20directly%20undercuts%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20other%20appropriations%2C%20The%20President%20may%2C%20as%20Commander%20in%20Chief%2C%20direct%20that%20such%20appropriations%20be%20used%20to%20cover%20military%20salaries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20money%20is%20likely%20coming%20from%20the%20Pentagon's%20standard%20research%20and%20development%20budget%2C%20but%20the%20administration%20did%20not%20provide%20more%20information%20on%20what%20money%20is%20specifically%20being%20used%20or%20if%20it%20had%20been%20bookmarked%20for%20a%20purpose%20other%20than%20stopgap%20military%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20other%20federal%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20like%20government%20contractors%20and%20agency%20staff%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-shutdown-federal-worker-pay-payday-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20not%20receive%20a%20paycheck%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20the%20government%20reopens.%20Troop%20pay%20was%20preapproved%20by%20Congress%20in%20past%20shutdowns%2C%20and%20members%20of%20Congress%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20aisle%20showed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2025%2F10%2F20%2Ftroops-showdown-trump-funding-00614874%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewillingness%20to%20pay%20troops%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20time%20around.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOn%20October%2024%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20said%20it%20received%20an%20anonymous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-friend-pentagon-donation-130-million-military-government-shutdown-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%24130%20million%20check%3C%2Fa%3E%20directed%20toward%20military%20pay%2C%20which%20the%20president%20said%20came%20from%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FAcyn%2Fstatus%2F1981463370558755229%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20friend%20of%20mine%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20particularly%20egregious%20choice%20when%20you%20have%20the%20option%20to%20do%20the%20legal%20thing%20and%20Congress%20has%20signaled%20that%20it's%20willing%20to%20do%20the%20legal%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Devin%20O'Connor%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20for%20Budget%20and%20Policy%20Priorities%20and%20former%20Office%20of%20Management%20and%20Budget%20official%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BConceptually%2C%20it%20opens%20up%20an%20enormously%20dark%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20also%20called%20for%20federal%20law%20enforcement%20members%2C%20such%20as%20deportation%20officers%2C%20air%20marshals%2C%20border%20patrol%2C%20and%20Secret%20Service%2C%20to%20receive%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20checks%26quot%3B%20for%20overtime%20hours%20and%20missed%20pay%20during%20the%20shutdown.%20The%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20this%20money%20is%20coming%20from%20DHS%20allocations%20in%20the%20One%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%20Act%2C%20a%20law%20that%20allocates%20billions%20toward%20%26quot%3Bactivities%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security's%20mission%20to%20safeguard%20the%20borders%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20between%202025%20and%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20ways%20in%20which%20what%20they're%20doing%20on%20law%20enforcement%20could%20be%20totally%20kosher%2C%20or%20maybe%20is%20more%20of%20a%20stretch%2C%20or%20they%20could%20just%20be%20doing%20something%20super%20illegal%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Connor%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20actually%20know%20because%20we%20don't%20have%20their%20justification.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20money%20moves%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20announced%20in%20October%20that%20it's%20funneling%20%24300%20million%20in%20tariff%20revenue%20to%20fund%20the%20Special%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Program%20for%20Women%2C%20Infants%2C%20and%20Children%20(WIC)%20program%20during%20the%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Berger%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20CBPP%20and%20former%20OMB%20official%2C%20said%20the%20money%20that%20is%20being%20used%20in%20this%20case%20is%20probably%20revenue%20collected%20in%202024%20that%20was%20initially%20allocated%20for%20Children's%20Nutrition%20Programs%2C%20like%20school%20lunches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20think%20of%20that%20as%20an%20example%20of%20them%20misrepresenting%20what%20they're%20doing%20for%20political%20purposes%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%20said%2C%20but%20it's%20likely%20still%20legitimate%20for%20Trump%20to%20use%20this%20money%20because%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20an%20existing%20transfer%20authority%26quot%3B%20to%20spend%20it%20on%20nutrition%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerger%20also%20referred%20to%20Trump's%20ballroom%20renovation%20of%20the%20East%20Wing.%20Congress%20does%20not%20have%20to%20approve%20changes%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20but%20major%20construction%20projects%20often%20require%20federal%20funding%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20granted%20by%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20fund%20the%20roughly%20%24250%20million%20project%2C%20the%20president%20is%20relying%20on%20money%20from%20a%20personal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-settlement-is-helping-fund-trumps-white-house-demolition-ballroom-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20settlement%20with%20YouTube%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20along%20with%20potential%20donations%20from%20major%20company%20leaders%20and%20his%20own%20funds%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20White%20House%20Ballroom%20is%20being%20privately%20funded%20by%20many%20generous%20Patriots%2C%20Great%20American%20Companies%2C%20and%2C%20yours%20truly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.com%2F%40realDonaldTrump%2Fposts%2F115408594704490513%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober%2020%20Truth%20Social%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Top%20execs%20at%20companies%20like%20Blackstone%2C%20Palantir%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20are%20also%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-white-house-ballroom-donors-list-apple-meta-amazon-microsoft-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguest%20list%20for%20an%20upcoming%20donor%20dinner%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20policy%20analysts%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20additionally%20pointed%20toward%20federal%20funding%20cuts%20for%20public%20health%2C%20nonprofits%2C%20and%20benefit%20programs%20in%20recent%20months.%20Congressional%20appropriations%20go%20both%20ways%2C%20they%20said.%20Opting%20not%20to%20spend%20money%20that%20lawmakers%20have%20already%20budgeted%20for%20could%20also%20be%20an%20example%20of%20executive%20overreach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20mentioned%20legal%20precedents%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Flegal%2Fappropriations-law%2Fimpoundment-control-act%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EImpoundment%20Control%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Flegal%2Fappropriations-law%2Fresources%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnti-Deficiency%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20intended%20to%20prevent%20government%20overspending%20and%20outline%20specific%20situations%20in%20which%20the%20president%20could%20override%20a%20funding%20appropriation.%20Examples%20of%20Trump's%20impounding%20funds%20include%20his%20previous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-usaid-funding-freeze-layoffs-furloughs-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancellations%20of%20foreign%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20USAID%20or%20the%20cancellation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2025%2F10%2F01%2Fnx-s1-5559386%2Ftrump-freezes-18-billion-in-funding-for-nyc-home-to-key-democratic-leaders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20infrast