C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68fef5970be9845f2dc52055%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELithuania%20closed%20Vilnius%20airport%20on%20Sunday%2C%20marking%20the%20third%20night%20in%20a%20row%20that%20it's%20temporarily%20suspended%20operations.%3Cp%3EPETRAS%20MALUKAS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELithuania%20said%20on%20Sunday%20that%20balloons%20flying%20from%20Belarus%20are%20forcing%20airport%20shutdowns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOfficials%20said%20the%20balloons%20are%20likely%20for%20smuggling%20cigarettes%2C%20but%20still%20pose%20an%20air%20safety%20threat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELithuania's%20prime%20minister%20has%20blamed%20Minsk%20for%20allowing%20the%20balloons%20to%20%26quot%3Brun%20wild.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBalloons%20flying%20in%20from%20Belarus%20have%20prompted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimages-show-nato-ally-lithuania-plan-to-blunt-russian-invasion-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eofficials%20in%20Lithuania%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20close%20local%20airports%20for%20a%20third%20night%20in%20a%20row.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Sunday%20evening%20that%20the%20airspace%20around%20Vilnius%20Airport%20had%20been%20temporarily%20suspended%2C%20affecting%20some%2047%20flights%20from%209%3A42%20p.m.%20to%204%3A30%20a.m.%20the%20next%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccording%20to%20initial%20information%2C%20the%20decision%20regarding%20airspace%20restrictions%20was%20made%20due%20to%20balloons%20flying%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Vilnius%20Airport%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20is%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20string%20of%20reports%20this%20week%20from%20Lithuania%2C%20a%20NATO%20member%2C%20that%20helium-filled%20balloons%20have%20been%20entering%20its%20territory%20from%20the%20Belarusian%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Lithuanian%20Prime%20Minister%20Inga%20Ruginiene%20said%20a%20%26quot%3Blarge%20group%20of%20smuggling%20meteorological%20balloons%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbelarus-says-boosting-military-on-ukraine-border-calls-it-enemy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaunched%20from%20Belarus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20into%20her%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20airport%2C%20in%20Kaunas%2C%20had%20to%20be%20closed%20as%20a%20result%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prime%20minister%20added%20that%20the%20balloons%20are%20likely%20used%20for%20smuggling%20cigarettes%2C%20but%20blamed%20the%20Russia-aligned%20leader%20of%20Belarus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-alexander-lukashenko-closer-look-at-the-belarusian-dictator-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlexander%20Lukashenko%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20allowing%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Brun%20wild.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20statement%20on%20Sunday%2C%20Rugiene%20said%20that%20Lithuania%20was%20temporarily%20closing%20its%20borders%20with%20Belarus%20as%20its%20security%20council%20meets%20on%20Monday%20to%20discuss%20next%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELithuania%20has%20been%20dealing%20with%20balloons%20from%20Belarus%20for%20some%20time.%20In%20September%202024%2C%20border%20authorities%20said%20250%20balloons%20had%20crossed%20over%20in%20a%20single%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20country%20has%20been%20raising%20the%20alarm%20more%20frequently%20over%20such%20incidents%20over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20as%20the%20Baltic%20states%20report%20repeated%20airspace%20violations%20from%20Russia%2C%20which%20counts%20Belarus%20among%20its%20closest%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELithuanian%20authorities%20said%20this%20week's%20first%20balloons%20started%20showing%20up%20days%20before%20and%20had%20already%20prompted%20an%20earlier%20airport%20closure.%20On%20Wednesd